  "description": "LFO1 on drama creates a slow tidal oscillation of coupling strength — partials wash toward synchrony, then recede into chaos, then return. The cycle is 50 seconds, roughly the period of ocean swell. Each wave leaves harmonic deposits: clusters that formed during high-sync persist briefly into the recession.",
